Okay, see how this pillar of frozen blocks stretches to the top of the screen? Well, that's where the secret exit is. However, I'm not going for it this time. I'll come back for it on my second trip through the level.
Too bad his cloud is too low for me to ride in, but what would I use it for underwater?
Assuming I can combo correctly...
Hello, and welcome back to Super Marina World! Now, where will I be going today? Well, let me just get to the "center of the universe" and take a look at the voting results here...

Alright, this makes the path to 6-B fully visible (even though I could already use it because of... reasons). Now, 7-3 and 9-6 tied for second, so which one should I go to next? Well, that's for the tie-breaker round to decide!

So, 7-3 is my next destination! Oh, by the way, where could I find the exact port of Ievan Polkka that was used as the invincibility music in ASMT? (NOTE: 8azaz22 gave me a link to the .txt file for that song. Thanks! I've put that link in the video description.)
Oh, man! Look at all them goodies! First let me carefully get the star coin and the 1♥P...

15-life combo! Also did you notice that that last moving pipe suddenly became cutoff when I hit the goal? (When raocow played this part, that last moving pipe sprite didn't even spawn, likely due to the sprite limit, and was just a cutoff pipe to begin with.)
Hmm... For some reason, I think this level will involve some blocks of the frozen variety.
Oh, man. How am I supposed to enter this pipe?
Whoops! I intended to spin jump kill that Bob-omb for an extra 1♥P, but it exploded (and got cape-thwacked) just before I stomped it. Also, that pipe obviously goes places, so let's check it out.

Why haven't they fixed this stupid glitch yet? There's no way they don't know about it, right? Should I try sending feedback regarding this glitch again?
